narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: learn c++, polymorphism, design paradigmsdon't think you won't learn anything because you know Java. That just makes you an arrogant asshole. You know who you are.

A substantial portion of this class involves learning C++, which could be a plus or a minus depending on your interests. Apart from the application of object-oriented practices to programming in C++, the non-C++ specific part of the course more or less came down to a few weeks of design patterns.

It's an easy class that babysits you learning C++. Some OOP design patterns are covered but there's too little focus on each method. Homework assignments are relatively easy but they dont weigh that much. Having to write a 8-15 page report in adddition to coding for the term project is annoying.
CS427 is a good course if you want to learn C++.

I would only recommend it as a relatively easy cs elective. You don't learn too much from the class unless you have never programmed in C++. Most of the topics you could probably learn by reading a guide to C++.
